{{Quote|They were the Lost Jedi, you know. The true Jedi, upon which the future will be built. They simply needed a leader, and a teacher.|Kreia|<ref name="TSL" />}}
The '''Lost Jedi''' were [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] who lived in the [[Dark Wars|aftermath]] of the [[Jedi Civil War]].<ref name="Chronicles">{{LucasArts|url=games/swkotor_sithlords|text=''Chronicles of the Old Republic''|int=Chronicles of the Old Republic}}</ref> The term commonly referred to members of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] who survived under the [[First Jedi Purge]] that was waged by [[Darth Sion]] and [[Darth Nihilus]]' [[Sith Triumvirate|Dark Jedi faction]], although the [[Exile (punishment)/Legends|exiled]] Jedi and former leader of [[Darth/Legends|Darths]] Sion and Nihilus' [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] remnant, [[Kreia]], referred to the followers of her [[Teacher/Legends|student]] and fellow exiled Jedi, [[Meetra Surik]], as the Lost Jedi; the true Jedi who would form the basic of a new generation of leadership in the Jedi Order.<ref name="TSL" />

==Lost Jedi==
===Knights of the old Order===
{{Quote|Take your ship, seek them out. If you find them, encourage them to gather on Dantooine&mdash;from there, we can call a Council and see what can be done.|Atris speaks to Meetra Surik regarding the Lost Jedi|<ref name="TSL" />}}
[[File:LostJedi-KOTOR2.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Surviving members of the Jedi Council were known as Lost Jedi.]]
[[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] and [[Jedi Council/Legends|Councilors]] [[Zez-Kai Ell]], [[Kavar]], [[Vrook Lamar]], [[Lonna Vash]], and [[Atris]], were Lost Jedi,<ref name="Prima">[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords: Prima Official Game Guide|''Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords'': Prima Official Game Guide]]</ref> as was [[Deesra Luur Jada]].<ref name="Jedi v Sith">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> Master Vash travelled to [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]], although she was murdered by [[Darth Sion]]. Atris resided in her [[Telosian Jedi Academy|secret Jedi Academy]] on [[Telos IV]], unknown to the Sith and Jedi alike, as she was to attend the [[Conclave at Katarr|conclave on Katarr]] and was assumed to have died there. Just prior to the [[Battle of Telos IV]], as agreed with her, [[Meetra Surik]] had what remained of the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]] assembled on [[Dantooine/Legends|Dantooine]], but again Atris would not expose herself.<ref name="TSL" />

===True Jedi===
====History====
Vrook, Kavar, and Zez-Kai Ell all fell to the coming of [[Kreia]], who murdered them in the ruins of the [[Jedi Enclave]]. After being defeated by Surik, Kreia referred to her student's disciples as the "true Jedi" upon which the future of the Order would be built. Having pledged themselves to Meetra Surik, the true Jedi became the foundation of a new Jedi Order.<ref name="TSL" />

====Members====
=====Atton Rand=====
{{Main|Atton Rand}}
{{Quote|I wanted no more of Jedi, or Dark Jedi, or the Force. I just wanted to be left alone. And then I met you on Peragus. And I thought, maybe, maybe she had saved me so that I could help you. ''[&hellip;]'' Once, a Jedi showed me the Force&mdash;I heard it, I felt it. At the time, there was to much pain to confront it&mdash;because if I did, it meant I would be changed into something else. ''[&hellip;]'' I want to learn how to use the Force. I want to learn how to use the Force to help you.|Atton, to the Jedi Exile|<ref name="TSL" />}}
Atton Rand, referred to as "the fool" by Kreia, desired no more than for external forces of the galaxy's conflict of light and dark to leave him be. However, having become acquainted with the Jedi Exile after meeting her at the [[Peragus Mining Facility]], Rand confronted his past and pledged himself to the exile, deciding to be trained by the former Jedi, the last Jedi, the true Jedi, in order to help her.<ref name="TSL" />

=====Brianna=====
{{Main|Brianna}}
{{Quote|I&hellip; I am the last of the Handmaidens no longer. I am Brianna, disciple of the last of the Jedi, and the one who will stand with you against all enemies who face us.|Brianna, to the Jedi Exile|<ref name="TSL" />}}
The [[Echani/Legends|Echani]] hybrid [[Brianna]] (initially addressed to as "Handmaiden", and referred to as "the servant of Atris" by Kreia), who was once one of Atris' [[Handmaiden Sisters]], was one of the Lost Jedi.<ref name="Brianna">{{DB|character|brianna|Brianna}}</ref> According to Kreia's predictions, the Echani would succeed Atris as the Order's leading [[Jedi historian]].<ref name="TSL" />

=====Mical=====
{{Main|Mical}}
{{Quote|I knew at that moment, that if you would no longer be a Jedi, then you must be correct. I realized I did not want to be a Jedi - instead, I wished to follow your path. ''[&hellip;]'' My master - the one intended for me - left to fight in the Mandalorian Wars. Now she has returned, and I ask her now if she will train me in the ways of the Force. ''[&hellip;]'' The one who was to be my Master was lost at Malachor V. I want you to teach me the ways of the Force. To become a Jedi Knight, what I meant to be.|Mical, to Meetra Surik|<ref name="TSL" />}}
[[File:Podisciple.jpg|thumb|right|Mical was both a Jedi survivor and a follower of Meetra Surik.]]
Following Surik's departure for the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]], [[Mical]], referred to by Kreia as "the disciple," sat on the new Jedi High Council as a Jedi Master, and sentenced Atris<ref name="CG">''[[Knights of the Old Republic Campaign Guide]]''</ref>&mdash;who had by then chosen to let go of her obsession with the Jedi and the dark side of the Force<ref name="TSL" />&mdash;for her crimes.<ref name="CG" />

=====Mira=====
{{Main|Mira}}
{{Quote|I want to become like you. I want to be strong! I don't want to be afraid or alone anymore.I&hellip; I&hellip; I don't want to keep running, and looking, and never feel like I'm finding what I'm looking for. I'm tired of being hunted. When the galaxy takes something from me, I want the power to let go&hellip; and I want the power to heal the echo when it's gone.|Mira, to the Jedi Exile|<ref name="TSL" />}}
Mira, referred to as "the huntress" by Kreia, was once a restless [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] who sought to be in a living environment&mdash;on [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]], where despite the misery of the place, the people there were active, their movements constant. When Mira awakened from her ignorance of the Force that connected all things, she became overwhelmed by the echoes of the Force that emanated from Nar Shaddaa's denizens. However, the Jedi Exile taught her to calm her mind in the Force, allowing Mira to sense the ebb and flow of life without succumbing to its frenzy.<ref name="TSL" />

=====Bao-Dur=====
{{Main|Bao-Dur}}
{{Quote|Having you here has an effect on me, General. I never noticed it years ago. I think my mind was too occupied then. ''[&hellip;]'' I feel... calm. More in control. The anger is still there, but I can feel it drifting away. The last years of my life have been defined by it. - the Mandalorians, Czerka and Revan. ''[&hellip;]'' My hands destroyed the Mandalorians. I can never be forgiven for that. ''[&hellip;]'' Under your guidance, I feel like I can overcome my anger.|Bao-Dur, to the Jedi Exile|<ref name="TSL" />}}
Bao-Dur, referred to as "the alien" by Kreia, is an [[Iridonian (species)|Iridonian]] [[Zabrak/Legends|Zabrak]] who was originally an [[Engineer/Legends|engineer]] that served under Meetra Surik during the Mandalorian Wars. His creation and activation of the [[Mass Shadow Generator/Legends|Mass Shadow Generator]] on [[Malachor V]] resulted in mass casualties from both the Republic and the Mandalorian fleet - as well as the utter devastation of the planet's surface; he also lost his right arm and replaced it with a mechanical one. Bao-Dur, a decade later, would reunite with his former general during their mission to find the lost members of the Jedi Council. With the Exile's help, Bao-Dur conquered his anger, and would follow his general in her footsteps - the footsteps of a Jedi.

=====Visas Marr=====
{{Main|Visas Marr}}
{{Quote|The death of my homeworld will always have its place within me, but it no longer dictates my future. I wish to learn the ways of the Force from one who has already faced that pain, and to use it to save the galaxy from those who would do it harm|Visas Marr, to the Exile after the defeat of Darth Nihilus|<ref name="TSL" />}}
The [[Miraluka/Legends|Miraluka]] Visas Marr, referred to as "the Blinded One" by Kreia, would return to her homeworld of [[Katarr/Legends|Katarr]] and finally see the destruction that [[Darth Nihilus]] had caused to her now-barren world; she would ask the Exile to teach her to use the Force to save the galaxy from harm.

